\li2 
\v 5 The youngest one was Ithream, whose mother was Eglah, \add another one of\add* David’s wives.
\li2 Those sons of David were all born in Hebron.
\s1 Abner decided that David would be king of all of them
\p 
\v 6 \w While|strong="H1961"\w* \w those|strong="H2388"\w* \w who|strong="H4421"\w* wanted \w Saul|strong="H7586"\w*’s son \w to|strong="H1961"\w* rule \w over|strong="H2388"\w* \w them|strong="H1961"\w* \w and|strong="H1004"\w* \w those|strong="H2388"\w* \w who|strong="H4421"\w* wanted \w David|strong="H1732"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* rule \w over|strong="H2388"\w* \w them|strong="H1961"\w* \w continued|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w fight|strong="H4421"\w* \w against|strong="H4421"\w* each other, Abner \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w becoming|strong="H1961"\w* \w more|strong="H1961"\w* influential among \w those|strong="H2388"\w* \w who|strong="H4421"\w* wanted \w Saul|strong="H7586"\w*’s son \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H2388"\w* king.
