\c 12
\s1 Nathan rebuked David
\p 
\v 1 \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \add told the prophet Nathan what David had done, and he\add* \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w Nathan|strong="H5416"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* tell \add this story to\add* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*: “\add I heard about\add* \w two|strong="H8147"\w* \w men|strong="H6223"\w* \add who\add* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* living \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* certain \w city|strong="H5892"\w*. \w One|strong="H1961"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w rich|strong="H6223"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w other|strong="H8147"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w poor|strong="H7326"\w*.
