\v 17 \add The priest’s two sons,\add* \w Jonathan|strong="H3083"\w* \w and|strong="H1980"\w* Ahimaaz, \w were|strong="H1992"\w* waiting \w at|strong="H1732"\w* \w En-Rogel|strong="H5883"\w* \add Spring\add*, outside Jerusalem. \w They|strong="H1992"\w* \w did|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \add dare to\add* \w enter|strong="H1980"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w city|strong="H5892"\w*, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w if|strong="H3588"\w* someone \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w*, \add he would report it to Absalom\add*. \add While they were at En-Rogel,\add* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w female|strong="H8198"\w* \w servant|strong="H8198"\w* \add of the two priests\add* \w would|strong="H1980"\w* frequently \w go|strong="H1980"\w* \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w* \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w report|strong="H5046"\w* \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w* \add what was happening\add*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w then|strong="H1980"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w would|strong="H1980"\w* \w go|strong="H1980"\w* \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w report|strong="H5046"\w* \w it|strong="H3588"\w* \w to|strong="H1980"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*.
