\v 31 \w Suddenly|strong="H2009"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w man|strong="H3605"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w Ethiopia|strong="H3569"\w* arrived, \w and|strong="H6965"\w* said, “\w Your|strong="H3068"\w* Majesty, \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w good|strong="H1319"\w* \w news|strong="H1319"\w* \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w*! \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w has|strong="H3068"\w* enabled \w your|strong="H3068"\w* soldiers \w to|strong="H3068"\w* defeat \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w those|strong="H3605"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w rebelled|strong="H6965"\w* \w against|strong="H5921"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w*!”
\p 
\v 32 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* said \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w him|strong="H5921"\w*, “\w Is|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w young|strong="H5288"\w* \w man|strong="H5288"\w* Absalom \w safe|strong="H7965"\w*/\w all|strong="H3605"\w* right?” \w And|strong="H6965"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w man|strong="H5288"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w Ethiopia|strong="H3569"\w* replied, “Sir, \w I|strong="H5921"\w* wish/desire \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w what|strong="H7451"\w* \w happened|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w him|strong="H5921"\w* \w would|strong="H5288"\w* \w happen|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w enemies|strong="H6965"\w* \w and|strong="H6965"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w those|strong="H3605"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* rebel \w against|strong="H5921"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*!”
\p 
\v 33 The king \add realized that he meant that Absalom was dead, so he\add* became ◄extremely distressed/overcome with grief►, and he went up to the room above the gateway and cried. While he was going up, he kept crying out, “\w O|strong="H3068"\w*, my son Absalom! My son! \w O|strong="H3068"\w*, my son Absalom, I desire/wish that I had died instead of you!”
\c 19
\s1 Joab rebuked the king
\p 
\v 1 \w Someone|strong="H4310"\w* told Joab \w that|strong="H5414"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w was|strong="H4428"\w* \w crying|strong="H1058"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* mourning \w because|strong="H5921"\w* Absalom \w had|strong="H4428"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*.
\v 2 \w All|strong="H1058"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* David’s soldiers became sad. \w Instead|strong="H2009"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* rejoicing \w about|strong="H5921"\w* defeating \add the soldiers who had fought with Absalom\add*, \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w were|strong="H4428"\w* sad \w because|strong="H5921"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w heard|strong="H5046"\w* \w that|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w was|strong="H4428"\w* mourning \w because|strong="H5921"\w* Absalom \add was dead\add*.
\v 3 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H5971"\w* returned \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w city|strong="H1931"\w* quietly, \w like|strong="H1961"\w* [SIM] \w soldiers|strong="H5971"\w* \w do|strong="H3605"\w* \w when|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H3117"\w* ashamed \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w ran|strong="H1961"\w* \w away|strong="H3605"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w battle|strong="H3117"\w*.
